caption: Delicious! And seriously interesting food. Amazing options for vegans and vegetarians. There is a vegan section of the menu so options are easy to find and  I recommend the eggplant soup. Food was exactly flavorful without being spicy.
Always love their Beef Kebab and have ordered it dozens of times. 👍

Very simple, yet FLAVORFUL food. The wait was a bit long, but that sometimes means your food is cooked fresh. And they did have a lot of take out orders to fill too. Our beef kebobs were tender and freshly grilled. Loved the saffron rice too. The veggie beef stew was different, but still enjoyable.
Excellent take out experience! Shwarma fantastic! Super duper nice staff.

Came here yesterday evening 2/20. I had the beef kabobs and hummus. The beef was cooked well, but it didnt come with any sauce. The hummus was just okay. The restaraunt is very small and cramped inside.
From the outside you don't expect much . But the food. Ah the food is just awesome . From the Dolmeh to kabab to khoresh sabzi. Hard to find better food and better value
The food is delicious and the staff is nice! I like that they have vegan options and highly recommend the vegan eggplant stew.
Intimate environment,  paid parking right next door. Delicious fresh shawarma!
Great food and good prices!!! Very tasty and calm environment.

Great food and service! Called the restaurant to make reservations and mike was great. Authentic persian food and taste. Ordered the koobideh, chicken & sultani with masto-khiyar, amazing taste and quality. THANK YOU mikeeee and koko persian restaurant!!
Great Food, Good Service, called Mike to make a reservation Thankfull to have persian food in Honolulu 🙏🏻
Good food for decent price!
it's OK, BUT WHAT REALLY TURNED ME OFF WAS THAT THEY CHARGE YOU A 2.00 FEE IF YOU USE A CC AND ITS UNDER 20.00...NEVER AGAIN
This place has delicious food. I could eat here every day.
Awesome
It's good Persian food on oahu
one of the only greek places here, and they killed it. great at taking special requests also.
Nice and cozy place for a great food. The quality is what you want and you for sure will get it. Suggestion: may call in advance to order the food for the time you want;if you know the menu!
Love this place for quiet weekend dinner with family.
Best food you will ever have in your entire life.
Legit Persian food, apparently the only in all of Hawaii. Very nice owner and server.
Small place with amazing Persian food. Tyler is very nice and funny.
Amazing food. Took a little bit to get it but was definitely worth the wait. Will be going back for sure.
Great persian food.
good food
Great food and service, will visit again
Small place, cozy atmospheric. Food is good but nothing special.

Looks sketchy from the outside, but it’s a really cute place on the inside. Food takes a little while to make because they make it as the customers order it, it’s delicious, well presented, and a reasonable size.

TIP: Get there early and try the appetizers. The place fills up quickly and seating is limited. There is a paid parking lot behind the building that costs $4. The ambiance is cozy, Persian music is playing in the background and the food is delicious.

We came in after 9pm, and were delighted to find they were still open. The hummus is some of the best I've had, and I would definitely recommend the Saffron Rice Pudding.  Excellent food, excellent service. We'll be back again soon!
It took a bit till food comes out, but it was worth it. Delicious food and kind staff!
Good food and big servings.
Okay food however service was not good!
Yes it takes a little too long for the food, but it is well worth it. Flavors are genuinely fresh and fulfilling. The ambiance is cozy and all you really need is good company and a cold beer 😉
One of the best Persian foods I have ever had in the US.

Finally a great place to get great Persian food! Excellent kebabs and atmosphere. Nicely decorated yet small interior. However, the food takes forever. It took 45 minutes for the food to come. That’s a bit much.  It was pretty good tasting but not as good as places in DC. knocking off a star for the long wait.

OMG!!! Amazing food and service. My girl friend is Persian and she was amazed at the authenticity of the food. We will be coming here every week now. Saying that we loved it would be an understatement.
Very tasty eggplant stew. Attentive waitress.
4.5 Stars - Delicious lamb and beef shawarma, and all the appetizers are also good. Big plus for consistency - been many times, never disappointed.

This place is absolutely killer. The ambiance was nice and comfortable. The food though, that’s what sets this place from anywhere else. It is absolutely delicious and accommodating to my wife and I being vegans. It is somewhere I will most definitely return to again. Excellent food and the carry out service was convenient.
Average persian food, a bit salty. Still a great option since persain food is so rare on the island.
Wonderful people with great food.

I wish i was able to see the zero star —The rice is like a week old —the place is so dirty and trashy —they over price food Took them one hour to bring the old food —the worse experience of restaurant i ever had —-balad nisty restaurant becharkhooni baaz nakon k esme ghaza irani ro kharab koni
Amazing persian food, I had their beef kebob and it is simply the best.

There aren’t many middle eastern food options on island. I went here because I was craving kebab. Order an appetizer so you have something to munch on while you wait for a fresh entree. I ordered hummus and beef kebab; it was some of the best kebab I’ve had on island!
Delicious food and great service. The dolmeh and shawarma were so on point! Highly recommend this place for tasty Persian food.
Best persian food ever!

(Translated by Google) Do not forget to serve the food with (Sumac) Sumac (/ sjuːmæk /; also spelled sumach, sumaq) A very special spice gives the food the delicious touch. They have vegetarian dishes and for those who hate vegetables you can exchange the salads for Rice or Bread. I in particular swapped it for more rice;) The meat is ground and come with a mixture of beef and lamb meat, the flavor is mild and I am not a lamb lover I tried it and it was very good.  (Original) No olvidar servir la comida con (Zumaque) Sumac (/ˈsjuːmæk/; also spelled sumach, sumaq) Una especia muy especial le da la comida el toque deliciosa. Tienen platos vegetarianos y para los que odian vegetales puedes canjear la ensaladas por Arroz o Pan. Yo en particular lo canjee por más arroz ;) La carne es molida y vienen con una mezcla de la carne Vacuno y de la carne de cordero , es suave el sabor yo que no soy amante de cordero lo probé y si estaba muy buena.

Great foods & friendly staff 🌹
The best persian restaurant
Good luck
It was FANTASTIC!The food, the service and the atmosphere in the place was outstanding! Many thanks! What an enjoyable experience!

Overall, well done so far. Just one suggestion, heat up the plates so the food arrives really hot, put the salad on a small seperate plate. The one dish they do great is the kebab as pictures show. I wish they had two people in service because you wait for long to get your order and things are missed like the dipping that usually comes at the beginning.
The best and only persian restaurant in hawaii.

One and only persian food in town.  It is conveniently located in the corner of Young and Piikoi Streets.  Parking is right at the premise for only $3. Very convenient.  Meat and chicken Kebob are authentic and tasty and the rest of their dishes are rare to find in town.  Real persian people prepare their food.  They serve alcohol as well. Prices are so reasonable. I strongly recommend this restaurant for those who want to try persian food.  Not a fine dining...just very casual.  Staff are very respectful and friendly.  Cool place!

Amazing Persian food!!! The beef and lamb shawarma is my go-to after work food. It is amazing and the staff here are always super friendly. Right away you will feel very at home and like you are among friends.

I ordered the Shwarma beef & lamb and In FL at pita plus I always got it with hummus,baba ganoosh, Turkish salad tahini and Shirazi salad..  And when I requested just to add the hummus to my Shwarma I was refused.  Not sure how long they're going to be around when they don't allow people to order food as they like it.  And it would've offset the over Tangy house sauce they used...
I eat here all the time!
Best middle eastern food I ever had! Love it and will recommend it to everyone!
I’m happy that the only Persian restaurant is up to par with Persian restaurants we have back home. 6 stars if I could add more
so juicy and so tender
very authentic and tasty
Best Persian food on the island!!
Great place, always convenient super good food love the Beef and lamb shawarma, the humus is great, and beef kabob plate another fav. Will always come back for more.

I’ve always wanted to try this place for quite a while now. This past Sunday I finally had a chance to. On my way another bar I glanced over and was like “oh ****! It’s empty.” So I walked in and sat at the bar.  “Slow night?” I asked. It was around 8 “No you just missed the rush.” The bartender replied.  It does always seem busy whenever I pass this place. Luckily, there were other events going on in town, I was able to grab a seat at the bar.  This is my first time at a Persian restaurant and really had no idea what to get or expect. I studied the menu and decide, oh kebab... I know what that is. So I ordered a beef kabab. I started my meal with hummus. Best hummus I ever had. It’s very light in taste - smooth with a hint of garlic and lemon. The pita bread was warm and soft. Wish there were more it because it was so good with the hummus.  Beef Kebab - I was a little disappointed with this one. Two grilled ground beef served with saffron rice, tossed greens and grilled tomato. The beef kebab was on the dry side. I expected some juicy meat as others have described it. It wasn’t tonight. (I had some hummus left so I dipped a few pieces of beef kebab in it, lmao). The rice was satisfying, the tossed greens, fresh!  The bar did not disappoint. Three glazed of vodka tonic and I was feeling good. Definitely better than the place I intended of going.  Oh yeah, I did have a cheese cake. I don’t remember if it was good or not. (I stopped taking notes - because, vodka!) I can tell you it was perfectly cut - look at the photo!
Very good restaurant love the food
Great little restaurant, amazing shawarma!

Food was ok. Coming from the mainland US and having access to many more options in regards to Mediterranean/Persian food, I would say this place was pretty bland. They don't have any sauces or the proper herbs that is put on this type of food. Customer service is great, I'm strictly referring to the food. Hopefully they can set the standard for this type of food on the island.

Great food and excellent service by Mr. Mahmood and his employees!  We ordered eggplant stew (khoresht e bademjan) and beef kabob (koobideh). Both foods tasted very good. The salad dressing was yogurt based which made it healthy and delicious. We would never thought that I could find a Persian restaurant in Honolulu. In my previous visit in 2008, there was no Persian restaurant. I am glad that we decided to try this restaurant after our conference.
The beef shawarma was the best I’ve ever had! So fresh and delicious!

This is my favorite place to eat on Oahu.  All the food is so friggin good, I literally eat till my pants are tight. My usual is the hummus and cucumber yogurt dip for starters, and the lamb & beef shawarma. The shawarma is absolutely delicious; if I could, I would fill a bathtub full of it, and just lie and feast there for a week, content in my gluttony. The hardest decision is eating everything, or saving some so I can continue eating the leftovers for breakfast. If you haven't tried this place, do yourself a favor and stay away, or you too will become a 200 pound shawarma addict.
I absolutely love their food!!! Such great recipes and very good quality food.  Very authentic.

Great Resturant, great people! I'm from northern California, we have over 15 Persian Resturant in our area, I could say Bar Koko was the best Persian Resturant I had so far over last 18 years, food is like home made, beef was well cooked and still jucey, price very reasonable compare to any other Resturant in Hawaii which they are usually expensive compare to California!
I like the staff because has kind and great attitude!
The BEST KEBAB ever!!! 🤙🏼

A cozy only persian restaurant in town. My favorites are beef and chicken kebob.  Authentic food as it is owned and managed by  a Persian family themselves.  Friendly staff and cool.  Alcohol is served as well. Prices are very reasonable.  Parking lot behind is accessible.  Easy to find in corner of Piikoi and Young Street.
The Kebabs are awesome.  I'm pretty sure they are made with love.  Thanks chefs. 😘 Small place with great service if you are in for a Persian experience.

I really wanted to like this restaurant..I have loved Persian food in the past and was excited to find this restaurant in my neighborhood.  I started with an old favorite of the Persian cucumber salad. It lacked flavor and the herbs that I'm familiar with. I could barely taste the mint and fresh lime. Next we shared the hummus. It was just ok and didn't have enough bread for the small portion. My entree was the Schwarma which was not what expected. I guess I didn't read that it was a little crumbly meat with copious amounts of lettuce and way too much house dressing. Again I think a restaurant is only as good as the food they are trying to traditionally represent. This place miss the mark for me..
Perfect food and service . Thank u chef SY from Houston,Tx
High five
The best Persian food I've ever had, taste like a home made food, nice and cozy place ,great staff
Good food and nice service. Beef kebab is highly recommended.
Very delicious beef kebab (kobide), friendly owner and waitress.
Great service and surprisingly great kabobs. We ate here twice during our two weeks on the island. On par with persian restaurants in DC.
Good exotic food and decent service but it took a long for the food to be served.

Well actually polite staff. However imagine koobideh with no raw onion and bread and sabzi beside!!! Or rice Not cooked fully no butter on it!!!! Low amount of food per course for the price!!!! Restroom not clean with staff wearing no uniform!!! They soon need to change their way and be a true representative of Persian Cuisine
It was amazing. I'm going back again today .
Great food, healthy food and good service
Love that they had vegan options! Eggplant stew and pita & hummus were delicious!

I had a Groupon and without it I never would have known about this Restaurant and I never would have tried Persian food for the first time.  It was absolutely AMAZING!! The Beef and Lamb Shawarma was Huge, fresh, delicious, and filling.  The restaurant itself is pretty small with paid parking in the back.  I will be purchasing as many Groupons as I can until it expires and will be back with or without a Groupon. Fairly priced.

The restaurant has great food, we really enjoyed ourselves, service was right on time, we were able to call our order in ahead of time so it was ready when we got there, they also do groups, the manager owner has a great personality and is there to make sure your experience is perfect, we did a Birthday get together with friends and everything was perfect, you can call and talk to a real person and they are always helpful. We look forward to going there again very soon.
Wow! Amazing authentic Persian food served here. Finally!!! Hawaii has a Persian Restaurant!
Awesome food! Right next to hookahookah which is perfect.
